                    <img src="/upload/width(100)/https://raw.githubusercontent.com/flyimg/graphic-assets/master/logo/raster/flyimg-logo-rgb.png">
                </p>
                <h2 id="hello-from-flyimg">Hello from Flyimg 2.0</h2>

                <h3 id="the-image-above-logo-has-been-served-using-flyimg.">The image above (logo) has been served using
                    the Content Delivery Platform.</h3>

                <p>How? Calling the source in the <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> like this:</p>

                <code>/upload/width(100)/https://raw.githubusercontent.com/flyimg/graphic-assets/master/logo/raster/flyimg-logo-rgb.png</code>

                <p>It got transformed from the original file which was 343px wide.</p>
                <p>Now, on the server, there is a cached version of this transformed image. There is no need to do the
                    transformation again next time someone requests this image.</p>
                <p>The best of all is that you get <em>Moz-jpeg</em> compression by default on all your JPEGs.</p>


                <h2 id="transformations">Transformations</h2>

                <p>You can do many different transformations to your images:
                    <ul>
                        <li><em>blur ( int x, int y, int width, int height )</em> blur a square in the image</li>
                        <li><em>crop ( int x, int y, int width, int height )</em> crop a part of the image</li>
                        <li><em>face.blur ( )</em> to detect faces and blur those faces in the image</li>
                        <li><em>face.detect ( int thickness )</em> to detect faces in the image, and draw a rectangle around them</li>
                        <li><em>face.pixelate ( int dimension )</em> to detect faces in the image, and pixelate them inside the image</li>
                        <li><em>format ( string format )</em> change the format of the image</li>
                        <li><em>height ( int height )</em> resize the image proportionally, with the specified height</li>
                        <li><em>pixelate ( int x, int y, int width, int height, int dimension )</em> pixelate a sqare inside the image</li>
                        <li><em>resize ( int width, int height )</em> resize the image without keeping proportions, with the specified width and height</li>
                        <li><em>square ( int x, int y, int width, int height, int red, int green, int blue, int alpha, int thickness )</em> draw a square in the image</li>
                        <li><em>width ( int width )</em> resize the image proportionally, with the specified width</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>

                <p><a href="https://github.com/kiboko-labs/flyimg" target="_blank">Check the docs for more info</a>.</p>
                <p>Happy imaging!</p>
